com.github.jonpeterson.jackson.module.versioning

Annotation Type JsonVersionedModel


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface JsonVersionedModel
    Specifies converter for used in resolving versioning for pre-deserialized JSON.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.Class<? extends VersionedModelConverter> converterClass 
      java.lang.String currentVersion 

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean alwaysConvert 
      java.lang.String propertyName 

    • Element Detail

      • currentVersion

        public abstract java.lang.String currentVersion
        Returns:
        the current version of the model; this will be added to the serialized model's propertyName().

      • converterClass

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends VersionedModelConverter> converterClass
        Returns:
        class of the converter to use when resolving versioning.

      • alwaysConvert

        public abstract boolean alwaysConvert
        Returns:
        whether to always send JSON data to converter, even when the data is the same version as the currentVersion().
        Default:
        false

      • propertyName

        public abstract java.lang.String propertyName
        Returns:
        name of property in which the model's version is stored in JSON.
        Default:
        "modelVersion"
